# Release version — keep two sources aligned

The published package version must match the runtime `__version__` string. They have diverged before (e.g. `__init__.py` updated without `pyproject.toml`).

When changing the release version, **always update both** in the same change:

1. **`pyproject.toml`** — `[project]` → `version = "x.y.z"`
2. **`control_plane/__init__.py`** — `__version__ = "x.y.z"`

Use the **same** semver string in both places. After editing, grep the repo for the old version to catch stray references if needed.

Optional: MCP `clientInfo.version` in `control_plane/acp_client.py` is separate; bump it only when you intend to change the ACP client identity string.
